  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      The <command>arpd</command> binary included in this package is dependent
      on Berkeley DB. Because <command>arpd</command> is not a very common
      requirement on a base Linux system, remove the dependency on Berkeley DB
      by applying the commands below.
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed -i '/^TARGETS/s@arpd@@g' misc/Makefile &amp;&amp;
sed -i /ARPD/d Makefile &amp;&amp;
sed -i 's/arpd.8//' man/man8/Makefile</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make PREFIX=/usr/local SBINDIR=/usr/local/sbin</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make PREFIX=/usr/local SBINDIR=/usr/local/sbin install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

